From: dongdong deng <ddeng@pek-lpgbuild5.(none)>
Date: Fri, 7 May 2010 16:45:07 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] comcerto: increasing DEFAULT_RX_DESC_NT value to enhance performance

The comcerto requested MAX_RX_DESC_NT*sizeof(tFDesc) DMA memory
for RX packages when init, but just DEFAULT_RX_DESC_NT chunks
memory be used when running.

Increasing DEFAULT_RX_DESC_NT could not waste the malloced DMA
resources and enhance the performance of comcerto.

Signed-off-by: Dongdong Deng <dongdong.deng@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/comcerto/comcerto_eth.h |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/comcerto/comcerto_eth.h b/drivers/net/comcerto/comcerto_eth.h
index 8f14933..f3950a5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/comcerto/comcerto_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/comcerto/comcerto_eth.h
@@ -34,7 +34,7 @@ extern const char comcerto_driver_version[];
 #define COMCERTO_DEV_WEIGHT 16
 
 /* direct EMAC0 control */
-#define DEFAULT_RX_DESC_NT 128
+#define DEFAULT_RX_DESC_NT 256
 #define DEFAULT_TX_DESC_NT 128
 #define MAX_RX_DESC_NT 256
 #define MAX_TX_DESC_NT 128
